\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Gross domestic product
\series default
 is the total market value of the final goods and services produced in a
 country in a time period.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A 
\series bold
final good
\series default
 is bought by its final user, whereas an 
\series bold
intermediate good
\series default
 is used to make another good.
