\series default
: Arrival of better, more expensive things biases inflation upward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Commodity substitution bias
\series default
: When prices increase, people buy cheaper alternatives.
 CPI basket is not rebalanced, so the increase in prices is overstated.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Outlet substitution bias
\series default
: When prices increase, people shop at cheaper stores.
\end_layout

