 says that the price level is fixed and aggregate demand determines real
 GDP.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Aggregate expenditure
\series default
 (which seems to be another word for GDP) consists of C, I, G, and NX.
 
\series bold
Aggregate planned expenditure
\series default
 is planned aggregate expenditure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The most important factors that influence consumption are:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Disposable income
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Real interest rate
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Wealth
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Expected future income
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\series bold
consumption function
\series default
 is consumption expenditure vs.
 disposable income (all else constant).
 The 
\series bold
saving function
\series default
 is saving vs.
 disposable income (all else constant).
 
\series bold
Autonomous consumption
\series default
 is consumption with no income.
 
\series bold
Induced consumption
\series default
 is the rest of the consumption, which people do because make more spend
